FSharp.abstractClassStubGeneration.description: Enables a codefix that generates missing members for an abstract class when in an type inheriting from that abstract class.

FSharp.abstractClassStubGenerationMethod.description: The expression to fill in the right-hand side of inherited members when generating missing members for an abstract base class

FSharp.abstractClassStubGenerationObject.description: The name of the 'self' identifier in an inherited member. For example, `this` in the expression `this.Member(x: int) = ()`

FSharp.addFsiWatcher.description: Enables a panel for FSI that shows the value of all existing bindings in the FSI session

FSharp.analyzersPath.description: Directories in the array are used as a source of custom analyzers. Requires restart.

FSharp.autoRevealInExplorer.description: Controls whether the solution explorer should automatically reveal and select files when opening them. If `sameAsFileExplorer` is set, then the value of the `explorer.autoReveal` setting will be used instead.

FSharp.codeLenses.references.enabled.description: If enabled, code lenses for reference counts for methods and functions will be shown.

FSharp.codeLenses.signature.enabled.description: If enabled, code lenses for type signatures on methods and functions will be shown.

FSharp.disableFailedProjectNotifications.description: Disables popup notifications for failed project loading

FSharp.dotnetRoot.description: Sets the root path for finding locating the dotnet CLI binary. Defaults to the `dotnet` binary found on your system PATH.

FSharp.enableAdaptiveLspServer.description: Enables Enable LSP Server based on FSharp.Data.Adaptive. This can improve stability. Requires restart.

FSharp.enableAnalyzers.description: EXPERIMENTAL. Enables F# analyzers for custom code diagnostics. Requires restart.

FSharp.enableMSBuildProjectGraph.description: EXPERIMENTAL. Enables support for loading workspaces with MsBuild's ProjectGraph. This can improve load times. Requires restart.

FSharp.enableReferenceCodeLens.description: Enables additional code lenses showing number of references of a function or value. Requires background services to be enabled.
FSharp.enableReferenceCodeLens.deprecationMessage: This setting is deprecated. Use FSharp.codeLenses.references.enabled instead.

FSharp.enableTouchBar.description: Enables TouchBar integration of build/run/debug buttons

FSharp.enableTreeView.description: Enables the solution explorer view of the current workspace, which shows the workspace as MSBuild sees it

FSharp.excludeProjectDirectories.description: Directories in the array are excluded from project file search. Requires restart.

FSharp.externalAutocomplete.description: Includes external (from unopened modules and namespaces) symbols in autocomplete

FSharp.fsac.attachDebugger.description: Appends the '--attachdebugger' argument to fsac, this will allow you to attach a debugger.

FSharp.fsac.conserveMemory.description: Configures FsAutoComplete with settings intended to reduce memory consumption. Requires restart.

FSharp.fsac.dotnetArgs.description: additional CLI arguments to be provided to the dotnet runner for FSAC

FSharp.fsac.netCoreDllPath.description: The path to the 'fsautocomplete.dll', a directory containing TFM-specific versions of fsautocomplete.dll, or a directory containing fsautocomplete.dll. Useful for debugging a self-built FSAC. If a DLL is specified, uses it directly. If a directory is specified and it contains TFM-specific folders (net6.0, net7.0, etc) then that directory will be probed for the best TFM to use for the current runtime. This is useful when working with a local copy of FSAC, you can point directly to the bin/Debug or bin/Release folder and it'll Just Work. Finally, if a directory is specified and there are no TFM paths, then fsautocomplete.dll from that directory is used. Requires restart.

FSharp.fsac.parallelReferenceResolution.description: EXPERIMENTAL: Speed up analyzing of projects in parallel. Requires restart.

FSharp.fsac.silencedLogs.description: An array of log categories for FSAC to filter out. These can be found by viewing your log output and noting the text in between the brackets in the log line. For example, in the log line `[16:07:14.626 INF] [Compiler] done compiling foo.fsx`, the category is 'Compiler'.

FSharp.fsiExtraParameters.markdownDescription: An array of additional command line parameters to pass to FSI when it is started. See [the Microsoft documentation](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/fsharp/language-reference/fsharp-interactive-options) for an exhaustive list.

FSharp.fsiSdkFilePath.description: The path to the F# Interactive tool used by Ionide-FSharp (When using .NET SDK scripts)

FSharp.generateBinlog.markdownDescription: Enables generation of `msbuild.binlog` files for project loading. It works only for fresh, non-cached project loading. Run `F#: Clear Project Cache` and `Developer: Reload Window` to force fresh loading of all projects. These files can be loaded and inspected using the [MSBuild Structured Logger](https://github.com/KirillOsenkov/MSBuildStructuredLog)

FSharp.indentationSize.description: The number of spaces used for indentation when generating code, e.g. for interface stubs

FSharp.infoPanelReplaceHover.description: Controls whether the info panel replaces tooltips

FSharp.infoPanelShowOnStartup.description: Controls whether the info panel should be displayed at startup

FSharp.infoPanelStartLocked.description: Controls whether the info panel should be locked at startup

FSharp.infoPanelUpdate.description: Controls when the info panel is updated

FSharp.inlayHints.disableLongTooltip.description: Hides the explanatory tooltip that appears on InlayHints to describe the different configuration toggles.

FSharp.inlayHints.enabled.description: Controls if the inlay hints feature is enabled

FSharp.inlayHints.parameterNames.description: Controls if parameter-name inlay hints will be displayed for functions and methods

FSharp.inlayHints.typeAnnotations.description: Controls if type-annotation inlay hints will be displayed for bindings.

FSharp.inlineValues.enabled.description: Enables rendering all kinds of hints inline with your code. Currently supports pipelineHints, which are like LineLenses that appear along each step of a chain of piped expressions

FSharp.inlineValues.prefix.description: The prefix used when rendering inline values.

FSharp.interfaceStubGeneration.description: Enables a codefix that generates missing interface members when inside of an interface implementation expression

FSharp.interfaceStubGenerationMethodBody.description: The expression to fill in the right-hand side of interface members when generating missing members for an interface implementation expression

FSharp.interfaceStubGenerationObjectIden.description: The name of the 'self' identifier in an interface member. For example, `this` in the expression `this.Member(x: int) = ()`

FSharp.lineLens.enabled.description: Usage mode for LineLens. If `never`, LineLens will never be shown.  If `replaceCodeLens`, LineLens will be placed in a decoration on top of the current line.

FSharp.lineLens.prefix.description: The prefix displayed before the signature in a LineLens

FSharp.linter.markdownDescription: Enables integration with [FSharpLint](https://fsprojects.github.io/FSharpLint/) for additional (user-defined) warnings

FSharp.msbuildAutoshow.description: Automatically shows the MSBuild output panel when MSBuild functionality is invoked

FSharp.notifications.trace.description: Enables more verbose notifications using System.Diagnostics.Activity to view traces from FSharp.Compiler.Service.

FSharp.notifications.traceNamespaces.description: The set of System.Diagnostics.Activity names to watch.

FSharp.openTelemetry.enabled.description: Enables OpenTelemetry exporter. See https://opentelemetry.io/docs/reference/specification/protocol/exporter/ for environment variables to configure for the exporter. Requires Restart.

FSharp.pipelineHints.enabled.description: Enables PipeLine hints, which are like LineLenses that appear along each step of a chain of piped expressions

FSharp.pipelineHints.prefix.description: The prefix displayed before the signature

FSharp.recordStubGeneration.description: Enables a codefix that will generate missing record fields when inside a record construction expression

FSharp.recordStubGenerationBody.description: The expression to fill in the right-hand side of record fields when generating missing fields for a record construction expression

FSharp.resolveNamespaces.description: Enables a codefix that will suggest namespaces or module to open when a name is not recognized

FSharp.saveOnSendLastSelection.description: If enabled, the current file will be saved before sending the last selection to FSI for evaluation

FSharp.showExplorerOnStartup.description: Automatically shows solution explorer on plugin startup

FSharp.showProjectExplorerIn.description: Set the activity (left bar) where the project explorer view will be displayed. If `explorer`, then the project explorer will be a collapsible tab in the main explorer view, a sibling to the file system explorer. If `fsharp`, a new activity with the F# logo will be added and the project explorer will be rendered in this activity.Requires restart.

FSharp.simplifyNameAnalyzer.description: Enables detection of cases when names of functions and values can be simplified

FSharp.suggestGitignore.description: Allow Ionide to prompt whenever internal data files aren't included in your project's .gitignore

FSharp.suggestSdkScripts.description: Allow Ionide to prompt to use SdkScripts

FSharp.trace.server.description: Trace server messages at the LSP protocol level for diagnostics.

FSharp.unionCaseStubGeneration.description: Enables a codefix that generates missing union cases when in a match expression

FSharp.unionCaseStubGenerationBody.description: The expression to fill in the right-hand side of match cases when generating missing cases for a match on a discriminated union

FSharp.addPrivateAccessModifier.description: Enables a codefix that adds a private access modifier

FSharp.verboseLogging.description: Logs additional information to F# output channel. This is equivalent to passing the `--verbose` flag to FSAC. Requires restart.

FSharp.workspaceModePeekDeepLevel.description: The deep level of directory hierarchy when searching for sln/projects

FSharp.workspacePath.description: Path to the directory or solution file that should be loaded as a workspace. If set, no workspace probing or discovery is done by Ionide at all.
